The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Actor   dead
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Actor   dead
                                  
	New Delhi, July 27 (PTI): Actor Ravi Baswani, known for his comic roles in films such as Jaane Bhi Do Yaaron and Chashme Buddoor, died today of a heart attack in Shimla. He was 64.        
	Starting his career with Chashme Buddoor in 1981, he established himself as a comic actor with cult film Jaane Bhi Do Yaaron which also won him a Filmfare award.        
	Baswani, also a prominent face on television, appeared in character roles in Bunty Aur Babli and Pyar Tune Kya Kiya.        
	A number of Bollywood actors expressed grief at his death. Just got to know that Ravi Baswani passed away. How sad and terrible. Wonderful man. A gypsy by heart. Always happy and helpful. RIP, actor Anupam Kher wrote on Twitter                                                                                                                                                           
